{
  "texts": [
    "where s f = diag(Σ f) -1/2 is the vector of factor return volatilities.",
    "The constraint that our portfolio return is uncorrelated (or has zero beta) with the ith factor return f i, under the factor model (14), is",
    "This is referred to as factor neutrality (with respect to the ith factor).",
    "It is a simple linear equality constraint, which can be expressed as a T w = 0, where a is the ith column of F Σ f.",
    "Factor neutrality constraints are typically used with active weights."
  ]
}